description:
Very few new imprints have received such a warm welcome from all sides of the spectrum than Room With A View. Respected dj’s, worldwide music media & retailers have all been deeply impressed by the quality & vision transported by the label founded in spring 2009 by Dairmount & Anja Knupper in Hamburg. The label’s ethic is aiming to get back to timeless “emotional content” club music with a futuristic flair, while breaking the pattern of “functionality” that club music too often slips into these days. Room With A View presents a subtle mixture of House & Techno with a twist of freshness & Detroit influences. 

It is quite a little performance to invite a large range of dj’s to enjoy the same sound these days : Techno mammoths such as Carl Craig, Laurent Garnier, Ritchie Hawtin, Dubfire or Dj Hell, Deep House heavyweights such as Jimpster, Dj Deep, Manuel Tur or Brothers Vibe, Tech House masters such as Steve Bug, MANDY or Joris Voorn, Leftfield wizards such as Lawrence, Peter Kruder, Jazzanova or dj legends such as Danny Krivit or Francois K have all embraced the sound of the label with real enthusiasm…

With over 11 years Production experience and 8 years DJing under his belt.
Cincinnati Native Mike Georgiton aka Vennatics is no stranger to the music scene.
Having multiple releases under various record labels over the years.
Originally producing and DJing Electro IDM and New School Breaks, 
until 2008 when he first got a taste of Dubstep.
Before crowds were ready for full Dubstep sets Vennatics would play
Fidget and Jackin house with a touch of Dubstep woven into the set,
to introduce but not overwhelm the crowds with the upcoming genre.
It wasn't until early 2010 locally when crowds fully began to embrace the genre, 
then Vennatics quickly became a staple in the scene.
In this last year Vennatics has become a crowd favorite locally and regionally.
 Vennatics currently plays a very Dubstep heavy set and usually throws in Glitch Hop 
,Fidget, And Drum and Bass to spice it up.
His sets are known for being very dynamic, and extremely high energy.

Vennatics Also hosts and is the resident DJ for Wobble Wednesdays in Cincinnati. 
It is a weekly night showcasing the best DJs in the genre.

Blu Bizness is composed of three native Californians, all sharing a genuine love for music. Original members Trefford Marien and Curt Barlage met while working at Off Beat, a record shop in Redondo Beach. As the primary vinyl buyer for the shop, Trefford was able to learn about new music. Both he and Curt picked up on innovative sounds, while developing similar tastes based on what passed through the shop. Eventually, the duo attempted production and found that in the studio, they clicked. Trefford brought the hip hop influence and I brought the in the old, rootsy type soul stuff, says Curt. But, we both had a love for jazz and we tried to incorporate many of the instruments used in that type of music. We combined those three elements hip hop, soul, jazz to create what we do now. In addition to Curt and Trefford, there was another mind behind the production of this initial track and all after; that man is Bobby Matus. His love for reggae, dancehall and other rooted music inevitably carried those sounds into Blu Bizness. Though their combined efforts in the studio have constructed encouraging results that are continuously evolving, the components of Blu Bizness have other artistic outlets, which only seem to add to their creatively diverse sound.

Composer-performer JOHNNY CHANG engages in extended explorations surrounding the relationships of sound/listening and the in-between areas of improvisation, composition and performance. Based in Berlin for more than 10 years, Chang relocated to his home country,  New Zealand in 2020.

Johnny is part of the Wandelweiser composers collective and in 2018, initiated a new framework for the presentation of creative research and performances, "Partitions & Resonances", aimed at encouraging collaborations between the varied disciplines of composition, musicology, historical research and performance.  Since early 2021, “Partitions & Resonances” has taken the form of a monthly listening series of compositions by Wandelweiser and related composers/artists/sound artists hosted by Audio Foundation, Auckland.

He currently collaborates with: Peter Ablinger, Jürg Frey, Antoine Beuger, Sam Dunscombe, Keir GoGwilt, Catherine Lamb, Klaus Lang, Mike Majkowski, Phill Niblock, Michael Pisaro, Derek Shirley, Germaine Sijstermans, Taku Sugimoto, Eric Wong.

As composer and performer, his articulated performances have been featured in: Staatsoper/ OperaLab//DAAD Mikromusik/MaerzMusik (Berlin), Donaueschingen Musiktage, Edition Festival (Stockholm), Sonic Acts Festival/Muziekgebouw (Amsterdam), Gaudeamus (Utrecht), Cafe OTO (London), Riverrun Festival (Albi), Q-O2 workspace (Brussels), Wandelweiser Klangraum (Düsseldorf), Minimal Jukebox (Los Angeles Philharmonic), Audio Foundation/Pyramid Club (NZ).

Biography:

In the summer of 2007, after having played at a beach-party together for the first time in Cannes, France, the Amsterdam-based producers Steve Johnsen and Sietze Rademaker decided to work together as The Disco Accidents.

The Disco Accidents produce music, remix and hit the dance-floors with an eclectic style of house, electro, techno, nu disco with a touch of rock ‘n roll. The Disco Accidents gigs are always full of energy, and fun.

Their DJ-sets were received positively by the international party audience. Soon more gigs followed with big parties in Cannes (Cannes Lions Festival), Belgium and back home in The Netherlands. They were often spotted in venues in Amsterdam, Rotterdam and Utrecht (Bitterzoet, Dancing on Leidsesquare, Paradiso, Girls Love DJs, Lowlands, Melkweg, 11, Flexbar, Apenkooi, Club Air). They did support-acts for their friends Gus Da Hoodrat, Jaime Doom and Ajax from the Australian Bang Gang Deejays during their European ‘Light Sound Dance’ and ‘D is for Disco, E is for Dancing’ tours and for Soulwax and The Glimmers. They also played at the 5 Million Hyvers (the Dutch Facebook) Party, together with Don Diablo, Erick E and Roog. The Disco Accidents were asked to DJ at the Dutch introduction party of the iPhone. And last but not least, they played at Holland House on a packed Trafalgar Square 2012 in the City of London.

Their name? Come and experience it yourself. It is true - Accidents do happen.

“Looking back at more than 20 years of nightlife, I wouldn’t want to miss anything I’ve experienced, because it got me to where I am right now. I have traveled trough different styles – house, break beats, drum and bass, techno..., because music has no boundaries.”

As a daughter of a Swiss mother and a Ghanaian father, Ajele was born and raised in Switzerland, where, at the age of eighteen, she got introduced to the electronic music scene and realized there were hardly any female DJs. Now that was something she strived to change! The decision was made and the first records, decks and a mixer where bought. Vinyl shopping became an addiction and playing them a passion. Since 1996 she’s an inherent part of Zurich’s electronic music scene.

2002 she started as a promoter with the label Chicks behind the Decks - a wake- up call for female DJs all over the country, to arrange numerous events and live performances across a wide spectrum of electronic music. This activity got her in touch with similar organizations all around the globe; new contacts were made and new projects born.

2004 was her first summer in Ibiza and for three seasons Ajele played five nights a week at the bar Lo Cura, one of the coolest hangouts in town. It would get her the attention of several promoters and on their booking lists. For instance, she became a regular for We love Sundays, Mulletover, Electric Lady Land, Tim Sheridan and Smoking Jo’s Nasty Dirty Sex Music at Space, Manumission at Privilege, Underground and Blue Marlin.

2007 Looking for inspiration in music and life, she moved to London for a year and back in Zurich, became a resident of the popular Hive-Club and a regular at Cabaret-Club (where she was hosting the event I feel you together with her good friend Susanna Grippo).

In 2008 she started producing her own tracks and teamed up with Klaus Amrein (aka Cooky) to form the project KREIS ZWEI. 2009 they received the "Electronic" award at the M4Music Demotapeclinic Contest.

In the past 10 years she took a step back from traveling abroad but she still has her regular gigs within the Swiss clubs and festivals. She is also a regular at the beautiful Kasheme living room, where she developed her smooth side. Playing her eclectic interpretation of a chillout set.

Her versatile and solid music style has given her many opportunities to open the night. Warming up the floor is her strength!

Rising from Oakland, California and fast becoming one of house music’s elite, Hector Moralez has paid his dues by working tirelessly from the bottom up. In demand at clubs and events throughout the world. Hector Moralez is renowned for his intelligent and soul awakening house music.
Hectors ambitions began at an early age of 17, where he would spend hours practicing on his decks with the vinyl he had just worked hard for at the infamous Primal Records. The knowledge gained from his experiences at Primal together with a long list of friends and contacts, allowed Hector to develop what has become his resourceful and creative sound. 

Whether in the studio or, performing live behind the decks, Hectors love, passion and energy is clear to see. His sounds take influence from Latin, jazz, funk, hip hop and soul and are of course sewn together with his apparent grooving bass lines and solid fat beats.
Hector’s character, hard work and innovative ability has given him a prominent standing in the house music scene, leading him to become one of the most sought after artists. Also forming the production phenomenon “Fries and Bridges” with occasional partner, Phil Weeks [Paris]. 

Releases from Hector have enhanced highly respected labels such as Music For Freaks, Nightshift, Detour, Vista, Brique Rouge, Doubledown, Lowdown Music and Robsoul. These popular works have lead to further demand with new releases due out throughout 2013 on Circus Recordings, Apollonia, Restricted Access, DJ Sneak Classics, Magnetic, Pacha Recordings and Robsoul. As well as managing and producing on his own distinguished underground labels, Minority Music & The Factory.

2013 saw his highly anticipated debut album with Chris Carrier, being released on the amazing new French imprint Apollonia. The duo formed a new (Live) Show "Lotus Seven" based on their LP which has hit International cities such as: Paris, Berlin, London, Birmingham, Miami, to name a few. 

Hector sets no boundaries as he expands the limits with his exceptional and versatile approach to producing and presenting his interpretation and version of house music. This attention to detail, evident in every beat, has led to acclaim from house music’s highest ranked artists "DJ Sneak, Derrick Carter, Doc Martin, Mark Farina, Chris Carrier, Diz and DJ Heather.

KEMP is a duo consisting of KZZ and EMP; two friends that happened to start working for the same company in Stockholm.

KZZ, who is one of the founders of the Swahili hip-hop group X Plastaz (www.myspace.com/xplastaz), began working on his solo project in early 2008. He soon realized he wanted to work with another person and asked EMP if he wanted to be involved. One cold January evening over some beers in a Stockholm bar, KEMP was formed.

The project is currently running alongside their fulltime jobs, making their spare days few and far between. That is why KZZ and EMP are living by their motto of Work now play later - Simple as that.

Mark is a producer of melodic and atmospheric, downtempo/ambient electronica from the small market town of Chippenham, Wiltshire in South West England.
In 2009, Mark began making his first music under the name Duane Barry, producing melodic, progressive breaks and quickly established a unique sound leading him to become a sought-after remixer for numerous labels .His original tunes also gained attention, in particular “Soft Light” which became a popular song on the summer festival circuit being played by Jody Wisternoff amongst others. 
Eager to share his love for the genre and push progressive breaks further, Mark provided guest mixes for various radio stations including Radio 1, Kiss FM, XFM, Proton and NSB radio and eventually began his own monthly radio show/podcast “Cosmic Refractions” on Dance Radio Global. Sharing the schedules with the likes of Paul Oakenfold , the show amassed  thousands of downloads every month and served as a promotional platform for the record label  Mark founded and operated -  Digital Sensation UK – a label showcasing new and established talent from the breaks scene which quickly became a popular staple for releasing futuristic and emotive electronica. Supported by DJ’s and producers from all over the world, DSUK was also nominated as Best New Label at the 2011 Breakspoll awards.  
During this time, Mark also released music under the project Innuendo - a more downtempo and cinematic take on his breaks music and released a handful of tunes to critical acclaim topping the downtempo charts on various online platforms and receiving tens of thousands of streams for his popular (unofficial) remix of “End of Line” by Daft Punk from the Tron Legacy soundtrack.  
In 2012, Mark released his first EP as Mark Allsworth – “Earth Exit” a cinematic, texture laden selection of tunes that received support and airplay from BBC Radio 1,Eddy Temple Morris at XFM and was included by Richie Hawtin on his Enter Ibiza 2013 compilation series. This was followed up by “Silent City” in 2014 which received accolades including support from the late, great Robert Miles on his Openlab radio station as well as having all tracks licensed to various compilations around the world.
A keen gamer (starting from the SNES/Megadrive era) Mark fulfilled the ambition of scoring the soundtrack to the popular indie video game Big Pharma in 2015 (PC, XBox One, PS4 & Switch). His score received 5 stars reviews at Soundtrack Geek and Soundtrack Dreams where it was also nominated for soundtrack of the year. 
Mark also currently makes music under the side project “Classified Sky” – an introspective, less-is-more approach to contemporary electronic/ambient music using warm retro tones and creative attention to detail which has been recently supported by Chicane on his Sun:sets podcast.
In 2019, Mark's original music was curated by the British Library to be included in the British Library Sound Archive to be preserved for and enjoyed by generations to come.

DUB4 (Skank It Up - FR)

Inspiré depuis toujours par la culture sound system, DUB-4 conjugue sa passion pour le Reggae et la Bass music en évoluant avec succès dans ces deux univers.

Des 2006 il fait partie de l'aventure Dubstep en France et introduit cette scène, émergente à l'époque, dans de nombreux clubs et festivals.
Refusant les clivages et les barrières de styles, en perpétuelle recherche de nouveautés, il se démarque rapidement par des sets éclectiques, riches en dubplates et exclusivités mêlant avec énergie reggae, garage, techno, dubstep ou dancehall.

Régulièrement booké sur les soirées de référence du genre en France et à l'étranger (Outlook festival, Fabric London, Plages Electroniques, Electropicales, SubDub Leeds, Telerama Dub Festival etc.), il est également résident et organisateur des soirées SKANK IT UP à Paris et Marseille où il invite aussi bien Boddika que Mala, Benny Page ou Mungo's Hifi.

DUB-4 a joué avec: Major Lazer, Zinc, C2C, Foreign Beggars, Mala, Benga, Feadz, Pone, The Bug & Warrior Queen, Iration Steppas, Jah Shaka, Mad Professor, Dope DOD, Prince Buster, Eek a Mouse, Michael Prophet, Mungos Hifi, Radioclit, Loefah, Boddika, Pinch, Kahn, Marcus Visionary, Benny Page, Scratch Perverts, Silkie & Quest, Goldie, Dillinja, Caliber, Radioactiveman, Stand High Patrol, OBF, Jahtari, Bush Chemists, High Tone, Tikiman, Mr Williamz, Solo Banton, Kenny Knots, Ikonika, Swindle, Von D, Pearson Sound, RSD  Smith & Mighty...

It was only a matter of time before Richard Banks would dedicate his life to music because being raised in a family of professional musicians essentially leaves no other choice.‚Ä®Richard‚Äôs first musical experience was focused solely on classical music, but at the age of 14, after 8 years of comprehensive education he decided to leave music school fed up with the arbitrary methods of teaching. He came back to music in college, but this time as a DJ, not a violinist.
Inspired by productions from Mood II Swing, Masters At Work, Blaze, Kerri Chandler, Basement Boys, Joey Negro, Knee Deep, and the likes, he fell in love with soulful and deep house and in March 2005 joined The Essential Productions crew, which al- lowed him to share his passion with a broader audience. His sound quickly gained recognition on the local scene which helped Richard to take over the residency in one of the most prestigious venues in Wroclaw ‚Äì Paparazzi Cafe Bar in November 2005. From then on the necessity of switching between club and bar environments gave Richard a constant motivation to improve himself, which helped him develop a sense of connection with enthusiasts of many musical genres while keeping his performance honest and passionate. In February 2007 another challenge came along, the residency at Pod Papugami.
Over the years, as his style evolved, Richard Banks managed to play alongside some of Poland‚Äôs best DJs (including K.Mill, Glasse, Easy, Rawski, Ricardo, Dudekk or Mmikimaus) and warm up the audience for international DJs like Catz N Dogz or Rocco (of Rodamaal fame). He had the opportunity of entertaining crowds of intimate venues (including Dekadencja in Katowice and Krakowska 180 in Wroclaw) as well as big spaces like the main room of Foksal 19 in Warsaw or the tent stage at Heineken Open‚Äôer Festival.
The turn of 2010/2011 brought a big change in Richard's life. He moved to Warsaw and started a very fruitful cooperation with Paparazzi, the Original Cafe Bar, which lasts to this day.

From the flat fields of Ohio to the concrete jungle of New York, Todd Sines' environments; real and virtual, have served as inspiration for his unique, hybrid sound. His post punk, industrial, and hip-hop upbringings, filtered through an obsession with analogue and early digital technology, resulted in stripped down electronic funk; before minimal was mnml -- it was just effective. Through his techno band, Body Release, with key Ohio players Titonton Duvanté, Charles Noel [Archetyp] and Mike Szewczyk, they dabbled in early rave sounds before embarking on their own paths. Todd's introduction in early 1993 to Detroit's Carl Craig and Daniel Bell resulted in seminal releases with Peacefrog, Planet E and 7th City by year end. Catching the ear of Richie Hawtin, "boiling point" was featured on his debut mix CD in 1995 on Mixmag. Soon after, releases on Andy Vaz's Background Records and Titonton's own Residual brought his sound to house and techno aficionados worldwide. Since his move to New York in 2003, he's worked with a variety of other artists, including !!!, Death in Vegas, Liquid Liquid's Sal Principato; he's remixed Alexander Robotnick, Paul Randolph, Robert Owens, Moonstarr, Adam Marshall, Lanoiraude and more. With his new material with Natacha Labelle on Frankie, he pushes the boundaries of house music, and with the resurrection of his .xtrak alias on YORE, his return to jackin' minimal funk reminds people of where it all started.

There are very few producers who managed to put their first production on a track-listing from a Radio 1 Essential Mix. Even fewer can claim that feat after being featured by Sasha, and to top it all off, during the Delta Heavy launch party at WMC Miami. It was no surprise that this debut production from Kris "One for the Road" was quickly signed to Hope Recordings, and was followed by the formation of the live electronic group Grayarea. Following a highly regarded guest mix on John Digweed's Kiss FM 100 show, AM Only picked up the rights to represent the group in North America and Grayarea took to the road for several headlining US tours.  Kris found solo success in his new home of Los Angeles, quickly becoming a resident for Spundae and Godskitchen, while his first solo production "Last Minute Flight" reached number one on the Balance Record Pool chart, and was included on Nick Warren's Global Underground 24: Reykjavik. A few years and several number one chart singles later, Kris is back in the Midwest, shacked up in the studio and aggressively pushing his agenda of on-the-edge, quality productions. His home grown imprint Nightshade Music has quickly risen through the ranks, mainly due to Kris' relentless pace and a keen ability to place music in the right places in the industry. Kris has been able to achieve through a simple philosophy of working smart. His debut Grayarea single was initially self released, giving Kris the opportunity to make the right connections and learn the proper channels to promote his music. That first release topped the UK Buzz and Balance Promote Group charts, receiving support from Sasha, John Digweed, Pete Tong, Paul Van Dyk, Dave Seaman, Timo Maas and Hernan Cattaneo, and was included on several compilations. Grayarea went on to release tracks and remixes for Bedrock, Silver Planet, Distinct'ive, Hybrid, John Digweed, Steve Porter & Thrill Kill Kult, with compilation appearances on Tiesto's "In Search of Sunrise 4", Ferry Corsten's Ministry of Sound, Global Underground and countless top DJ charts and playlists. Perhaps the most refreshing part of his success is the dedication shown to the vision of artistic future in personal life. It is a never-ending story of young artists making it big at first, then slowly fading away into our residual consciousness, and finally disappearing forever to some cubicle shaped reality that some insist on calling "real life".  Kris has shed all the artificial life ideas that our society drills into us every day. "Cold turkey" is the best way to get it done and after launching Nightshade Music in February 2008 he has never looked back. He has dedicated all his time to studio work, managing and promoting his label and touring extensively with his eclectic, funky DJ sets. Expect to hear anything from Rick James to Moby, 2 Live Crew to Kraftwerk, all mixed fluidly over a bed of infectious melodic house, progressive, techno and whatever he can fit into the groove. Kris has reached several recent milestones as a DJ, producer and label owner; 2009 marks his second appearance on the flagship Global Underground mix series (Darren Emerson GU36: Bogota), with tracks also featured on chart topping compilations from Armada Music (Simon & Shaker: Surfaces Vol. 1 and Blake Jarrell: Concentrate), and hit singles on respected labels Baroque, Ready Mix and his own Nightshade Music imprint, with top talent enlisted to remix his work (Manuel De La Mare, Tiger Stripes, Mazi). It should come as no surprise that this recent string of hits has kept Kris in demand at clubs across the US, Europe and South America. Kris's scope is not limited to the dance music industry, having recently licensed music (co-produced with Grammy nominee Bill Hamel) to Konami's 10th anniversary edition of "Dance Dance Revolution", with other commercial music clients including Heineken, ESPN, Crate & Barrel, MTV and Falken Tires. Kris hosts Nightshades on DI.fm and Protonradio.com, with the Nightshades podcast reaching thousands of listeners each month. Past guests have included Desyn Masiello, Paul Harris, Dirt Crew, Pako & Frederik, Thomas Gold and a rotating roster of label artists and supporters. Kris has been a staple on Fuel XM80 The Move, D:Fuse's top rated "People" on XM, and Chicago's legendary 'Sonic Boom' on Q101FM. Kris has performed at clubs and festivals across the globe; Ultra, Area:2, Vision (Chicago), Vinyl (Denver), Vanguard & Circus (LA), House of Blues (Las Vegas) to name but a few as the list keeps growing..... ..
*edited from an article written by Voytek Tusz for Exodus Magazine, Chicago

Born in Italy begins to make the first contact with the vinyl at the tender age of 13 years thanks to his father who owned several LPs, including a rare collection of Bob Marley, Peter Tosh and Jean Michelle Jarre etc. A few years later, and precisely to the 90's began using the first standard for home computers to create sample and audio tracks in 8-bit, through music cartridges that connect to keyboards such as the COMMODORE 64, followed in succession over the years as other computer SINCLAIR ZX SPECTRUM, ATARI ST, MSX PHILIPS II and the COMMODORE AMIGA 64/128 Bit. And from that moment it was love for music and creating music projects! Since then he has been a continuing search for the musical genre that's more fit is going from reggae, rock, metal, hip hop, garage, until in the far back in 1993 is beginning to discover at a party and underground and commercial music the first real love for the consolle so far unknown. Within a few years and managed to get lucky on a console with a 3-channel mixer with two direct drive turntables without pitch control and a cassette deck, was a complete disaster because without the use of the pitch and belt drive you could not mix two vinyl so discredited by what he gave up until he managed to put some money aside to buy 2 Technics - SL1200 and a little hard, but there was also a dilemma before and 'other love then , while that for 'House music began to be some records that still has its charms and moves a lot of heads, ie with INNER CITY BIG FUN GOOD LIFE and with Technotronic PUMP UP THE JAM. Over the years now finds new impetus to continue to obsessively in love finding new music genres that involve more and more and gradually increasing its cultural heritage by including in his preferences and inspire new generations as the modern DEEP, HOUSE, TECH HOUSE, JACKIN.

ING

  Carlo Battistini aka C. was born on june 1985 in Macerata.
  At the age of 15 he was found of music especially on dijing.
  In a short time he bought a second-hand consolle together with his two best friends (Al.essandro and Ma.rco) ,they set up C.AL.MA. project and they began to turn their first discs at private parties.
  After high school studies he moved to Bologna where he enriched his musical culture.
  During these years he developed his own style characterized by sounds which range from house sonorities to the wormest of deep-minimal.
  In a little more than a year C.AL.MA. began a collaboration with "Shape" association wich insert them as resident djs in the Playhouse events at Kindergarten,in Altavoz parties and in others important events around Emilia Romagna.
  With the passing of time he decided to walk in Al's footsteps moving his first steps toward the production world.

Hollywood Noo (pronounced New) is about to release his debut mix tape, “Noo World Order” on New Years Day, January 1, 2011. The release of “Noo World Order” will be the beginning of the Noo Year Campaign. The highly anticipated mix tape release is sure to be a success and create a buzz in the hip hop community as well as across the world. Noo is not your average hip hop artist, he is seen as a visionary, lyricist and a marketable artist. He can cater to all genres and styles of music making him stand out amongst the crowd.

"Noo is lyrically Rakim with a D.C. demeanor, A rap style like none other and swagg out of this world". --Rollo Williams. Soul World Entertainment.

In an era where Hip Hop is labeled dead, Noo tends to challenge that judgement and say, “Not only is Hip Hop not dead; but it lives and thrives in DC. His prime objective in the music industry is to have his hometown of Washington, DC recognized on a national level for rap, hip-hop and r&b; and not just for the adapted genre of music DC lives by daily known as Go-Go. He believes that it’s time for the music industry to come to DC and hear the talent.

In no way is Noo a rookie on the scene. DC Born and raised, Wayne Brian Barnes Jr.’s love for hip hop began at a young age. When peers were just beginning to walk and talk, he knew words to classic hip-hop songs such as Kriss Kross, “Jump” and Rakim, “Make em clap.” During his college years at Shaw University, he began his rap career with childhood friend and fellow group member Arnell “Young Pawn” Diggs, together they were the hip-hop dynamic duo by the name of “Too Kool.” Too Kool was featured in Shaw TV Magazine as “The Modern Day Kid n Play,” Kevin Parkinson of Vinark J. Productions. Too Kool released a mixed genre radio single called “Roll Call” featuring go-go group CCB locally in the DC area. The release got over 1,500 plays via Internet radio and myspce. The release was a great success and they recorded an unreleased remix of “Go-Go Power Rangers,” a worldwide kids television show which caught the eye of many radio stations in the Raleigh, North Carolina region. They soon became featured artist on the SHAW TV Mixtape Tour which they were headlined artist along with other up and coming artist such as The Weidoss, J. Ross, young Newz, Seen Phillips, D85, R and the Hat Gang which became a huge success and built a promising fan-base in the Raleigh, North Carolina region.

In April of 2009 Noo relaunched his solo career and hooked up with DJ Jarmz & DJ Premiere and Released “THE REVIVAL MIX-TAPE : DJ PREMIERE ADDITION” which was featured on websites such as Datpiff.com HipHopGame.com.

From the success of “The Revival Mix-Tape,” Noo gained a large following and in March of 2010 released a compilation CD for his fans called the Noo World Order Bootleg which featured unreleased tracks Noo recorded while putting together the Noo World Order Mix-tape.

In the Summer of 2010 Noo hooked up with Romulius Queen CEO of Forgotten City Productions and recorded numerous tracks with Forgotten City and their All Star Roster: Erika Anderson, Syrius Black, Bravo, E-Rock, Krown K and many others.

Noo released his first single off of the Noo World Order Mix-tape entitled “Bestfriend” produced by super producer Kajmir Royale via myspace, facebook, & twitter.

In August of 2010 Noo took the biggest step in his career and started his own label, Timeless Music Empire (TME), with long time friend Arnell Diggs-Martin, formally known as Pawn from the group TOO KOOL.

The single “Bestfriend” created so much positive buzz and rave reviews that Noo released his 1st official single “I think it’s my swagg,” featuring Erika Anderson produced by Super Star O.

This winter 2010, Noo has been seen performing at numerous venues and Open Mic spots. He also was featured on fellow DMV Artist Holleywood’s debut mixtape Sneakers & Speakers which was released December 21, 2010 on many hip hop blogs via Myspace, Facebook & Twitter.

Last but not least Noo is ready to release his mix tape “Noo World Order” on New Years Day, January 1, 2011. Stay tuned, Friday, December 31 the track list for Noo World Order will be unveiled.

Kyle Devine is a music producer based in Portland, Oregon, whose work is licensed by culture-defining brands including Nike, NISSAN, ESPN, the NBA and McDonald’s. His style is typified by sophisticated rhythms, classic and electronic instrumentation, celestial vocals and penetrating bass that move the listener hypnotically closer to its source.

Devine’s work can be heard in countless forms of media, from full-length albums to radio and television advertisements, YouTube videos and corporate presentations. 

As a young man, Devine was obsessed with hip-hop music and studied the production techniques of Dr. Dre, Timbaland and DJ Premier. Under the moniker Terminill, he began experimenting with the famed Akai MPC 2000XL, the same piece of gear favored by Kanye West in his iconic early works, and established a reputation in Portland’s hip-hop underground for producing industrial-grade beats. 

In 2009, he opened Devine Noise, a full-service recording facility based in North Portland's creative industrial district. Home to thousands of individual song and album projects, the studio served as a creative hub for musicians and audio technicians alike, and remains in operation under new ownership.
 
Today, he is a proud husband and father of four and continues to work full-time as a music producer, software developer and connector of the creative community world-wide.

Mink: Multimedia Project / Music Line

Das Projekt war Anfang der 90er Jahre, damals noch ohne Namen, in den Gründungswirren des KunstWerks Köln entstanden. Elektronische Kunst krankte damals daran, dass entweder die künstlerische Vision nicht handwerklich adäquat umgesetzt werden konn-te, oder das Handwerkliche zur Form ohne Inhalt verkam.

Die Idee des Mink-Projekts war, eine Kooperation von Informatikern mit den Künstlern des KunstWerks einzugehen, in denen die einzelnen Gruppen ihre jeweilige Expertise in gemeinsame Projekte einbringen konnten, mit dem klaren Anspruch, die Techniker sind keine Künstler, und die Künstler sind keine Techniker, aber durch Respekt und Kommu-nikation werden künstlerische Synergien geschaffen. 

Nach etwa einem Jahr bekam das Kunstwerk ein Problem. Nachdem einige Vorstände die Kontonummern ihrer Privatkonten mit denen der Konten des Vereins irrtümlich verwechselt hatten, mussten alle Projekte, die übergreifend vom Verein getragen wurden, eingestellt werden, so auch das damalige Multimedia-Projekt. Eine Sitzung des damaligen Mitglieder des Projekts ergab, wir möchten das Projekt nicht einstellen, wir haben dann die Vorstandsmitglieder aus unserem Projekt geworfen und das Projekt unter dem Namen Mink als Akronym für „Mink is not KunstWerk“ weitergeführt.

Between club gigs, radio, production work and now her personal label SoundSelective Records, Milly De Mori career has been steadily growing to a rounder artist profile.
Swinging from minimal house all the way to tecno, Milly De Mori's sophisticated and innovative touch is able to convey a certain "groove" yet unique underground mood to her DJ sets, well suited for both mainfloors or the smaller rooms.

While working in different clubs throughout Italy and internationally, Milly has been hosting for 7 years the successful radio show MILLYBAR on Radio M2O, Italy’s leader electronic radio station, mixing the best selections of promos and fresh releases in the underground tech-house/tecno scene.

For the past few years she’s been working regularly in the studio making music mostly solo, but Milly hasn't shied away from collaborations with Luca Doobie (Off, Freerange, Highgrade) or Berlin producer Inexcess (Still VorTalent).
Highgrade, Malatoid, Presslab Records, Kritical Noise Records, Stryke or her own SoundSelective Records are some of the labels she's released on so far.

 Fascinated more with tecky sounds and funky basslines than with vocals, Milly De Mori finds her roots in house music in the late 80's/beginning 90's, when hanging out in Ibiza she was first exposed to the 4/4's that changed her life.
Italian born living in Milan, Milly decided to move to NY in '93 where she spent 12 years, until 2005.
During her US stay Milly bloomed as a DJ creating a very personal style that quickly found a great response in the hottest markets like NYC, Atlanta, Miami and Los Angeles.
In 1999 Milly started SoundSelective.com, a pioneristic online-only-radio station, that webcasted some of the best house, deep house, teck house and tecno and offered alongside traditional programming rotation, weekly live webcast shows with audio and video straight from the DubLab LA’s studios.
Due to the WallStreet crash in 2001 and consequent fall of the Dot.coms', SoundSelective was forced to suspend the programming and streaming, and that left Milly De Mori free to pursue her DJ career and delve into music production. Today SoundSelective is a music service company catering to high-end fashion brands.

In 2005, as electronica was taking over Europe, Milly decided to relocate back to Italy to be closer in contact with the electronic contaminations coming from Germany and France. Since then she's been traveling and working regularly to Spain (Space Ibiza, Privilege, Razzmatazz), Tunisia, Germany (Rechenznetrum Berlin), London, the US (SF, NY, Miami) and throughout Italy (Magazzini Generali Milano, Tenax Florence, Frau Marlene Tuscany, Divinae Follie Bari and many others)

Deep, pulsating grooves laden with inspired sonic crescendos that ebb, flow, peak and trough: these are the inimitable sounds of Dubfunk, one of Progressive House music’s truly formidable talents. From humble beginnings in his homeland of Egypt, global recognition for the quality of both his DJ performances and forward-thinking productions has seen Dubfunk firmly establish himself as a key player in electronic dance music’s ever-evolving landscape. And, having achieved so much in so little time thus far, it’s clear that this master of grooves’ meteoric rise has really only just begun … 

Renowned for crafting seamless deep mixes of distinction, as a DJ, Dubfunk’s sets have gleaned global notoriety for their smooth programming, flawless transitions and constant, resonant groove. Fueled by an eclectic blend of childhood musical heroes (including Led Zeppelin, The Doors and Nina Simone) and inspired via an epiphany induced by the iconic Northern Exposure and Global Underground compilations of the mid-1990s; his trademark penchant for embracing diversity and concocting cohesive fusions of s

Armed with many years of professional audio engineering career and a rare creative ability to write music from the heart that makes his mind and body sing; Dubfunk’s productions are imbued with a sublime mixture of technical precision and delicate sensibility that, together, have forged a unique, emotive sound that is all his very own. Drawing upon a passion for sounds deep within the broad spectrum of electronic genres yet forever staying true to his roots, since 2007 his tunes have been regularly championed by DJs the like of John Digweed, Hernan Cattaneo, Sasha, Laurent Garnier, Slam and more; have made their way into the upper echelons of the world’s premier music download charts; and have consistently made their way onto a list of top-shelf labels including Global Underground, Audio Therapy and more. 

Furthermore, his association with these labels has in turn seen him at the helm of no less than six prestigious compilation releases: five for Global Underground (encompassing its ‘Electric Calm’, ‘Digitized’, ‘Synchronized’ and ‘5 Years Of GU’ banners) and one for Audio Therapy ‘This Is Audio Therapy Digital 2’. 

Constantly enthused and energized by the wealth of new sounds and electronic nuances that surround him, Dubfunk’s passion for music know no bounds. Although immensely satisfied with his DJ and production career, in 2007 he launched his own imprint: Dyami Records. Founded as a flexible vehicle for his own works and a catalyst for launching rising studio stars of today, tomorrow and beyond; Dyami specializes in forward-thinking tech-house & techno sounds, and has fast become a recognized seal of studio prowess and musical quality.

Chuck Cogan was inspired to get his own studio together after hearing Global Communication’s The Way in ‘97.
After a long healthy slog in the studio perfecting his craft, he was signed by Soul Brother records.
Releases on that imprint as well as Trunkfunk and Soul Phusion over the next five years backed by a healthy
DJing career was Chuck’s staple diet. However a few years ago he felt that the music was stale for him and almost gave it up.
Then in 2008 he returned to the studio and the first record to emerge was the sublime "Satellites".
His music making is solely for himself and now we here at solemusic are proud to release these heartfelt tracks.

Kevin’s music is best described as Pop-Americana, with a twist of “Blue-eyed Soul”. His musical roots run Gospel, Blues, and Country – with Elvis, Tom Jones, BJ Thomas and James Brown as his greatest influences. 
                Blending his own compositions with a fresh interpretation of many classic covers, Kevin’s “one-man-band” set list keeps the crowd on the dance floor, or on their feet. 
                A respected producer, recording artist and songwriter in Nashville’s underground music community, Kevin has shared the stage and studio with many of Nashville’s music elite.
                For over a decade, Kevin is sole proprietor of his own Production Company and recording studio -- Progress Music Nashville. His credits include Shelby Lynne, the Imperials, Charlie Pride, Gary Paxton, and a wide variety of established artists, writers and producers.

Ugoluna

Born in Caracas whilst living in many countries, this Spanish-Italian descendant currently based in London has been in touch with music from a very young age, raised on a musical background that varies within Rock, Punk, Pop and Fusion Jazz to even the darker edge of Industrial and Metal music, Ugo was enchanted with many musical instruments, particularly Drums and Percussion's, let alone being very faithful to these instruments even today.

His first connection with Electronic Music started in the early 90 ́s from Drum n’ Bass, Jungle and IDM and then into the late 90 ́s with the whole Rave scene. It was in the year of the millennium when he branched out and stormed into the world of Production and Djing. As a live performer it became second nature to Ugo rewarding dance floors with his very own deep and uplifting style, which is very similar to his drumming sessions. Composing and re-creating groovy rhythms with rare complex structures which offer a wide range of suggestive landscapes, all this characterised by the most epic elements of sound has been the drive of Ugoluna ever since. 

His introspective productions with a deep and intense vibe were the key on his inclusion on Henry Saiz’s label “Natura Sonoris”, releasing his first EP “World Solo Take One” at its beginnings. The Natura Sonoris label started a musical landscape holding different artists that shared a similar vision, a vision influenced by different elements: the power of Techno with the precision of Minimal and the hypnotic structures of Trance let alone the evocative melodies of I.D.M.

Since early 2004, Ugo has been offering various live sessions with many young, inspiring and established artists from the Electronic music scene throughout cities like Madrid, Dublin, Bristol, Caracas and London.
